ðŸ“˜ Overview

This project contains classic computer science problems implemented in Python, covering Backtracking, Recursion, and Dynamic Programming (DP) concepts.
Each algorithm is modular, commented, and easily testable for learning or interview preparation.

ðŸš€ Topics Covered
ðŸ”¹ 1. Backtracking Problems
Problem	Description
N-Queens Problem	Place N queens on an NÃ—N board so that no two queens attack each other.
Sudoku Solver	Solve a 9Ã—9 Sudoku puzzle using recursion and backtracking.
Knightâ€™s Tour	Find a path for a knight to visit every square exactly once.
Palindrome Partitioning	Break string into all possible palindrome substrings.
Tiling Problem	Count all possible ways to tile an nÃ—m floor with tiles.
ðŸ”¹ 2. Recursion Practice
Problem	Description
Indirect Recursion	Functions calling each other recursively.
Sum of N Numbers	Demonstrates helper recursion.
Even/Odd Checker	Uses indirect recursion logic.
Palindrome String Check	Recursive check for palindrome strings.
Basic Calculator	Recursive evaluation of arithmetic expressions with parentheses.
ðŸ”¹ 3. Dynamic Programming (DP)
Problem	Description
Fibonacci (Memoization)	Classic DP example.
Rod Cutting	Maximize profit by cutting rods into optimal lengths.
Longest Common Subsequence (LCS)	Find maximum matching sequence between two strings.
Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS)	Find longest increasing pattern in array or string.
Bellman-Ford Algorithm	Single-source shortest path (with negative weights).
Floyd-Warshall Algorithm	All-pairs shortest path using tabulation.
Dijkstraâ€™s Algorithm	Shortest path algorithm (greedy + DP approach).
Coin Game	Optimal game strategy using DP.
ðŸ”¹ 4. Advanced Problems
Problem	Description
Inversion Count (Merge Sort)	Counts out-of-order pairs efficiently.
Arithmetic Parenthesization	Maximize expression value with parentheses placement.
Piano Fingering Optimization	Minimizes movement cost between notes using 3D DP.
Wildcard Pattern Matching	Supports ? and * matching with recursion + memoization.
